# Backend Conventions

## API Structure

- All endpoints under `/api/v1/`
- Follow the project structure in `docs/architecture/backend.md`
- Layers: `api/` (routes) -> `services/` (business logic) -> `models/` (ORM)
- Pydantic schemas in `schemas/` for request/response validation

## Database

- Every data table MUST have an `org_id` column (NOT NULL) for multi-tenancy
- Use Supabase Row-Level Security (RLS) on all tables
- Alembic for migrations in `migrations/`
- Use SQLAlchemy / SQLModel as the ORM
- JSONB columns for flexible data (condition properties, measurement geometry)

## Auth & Permissions

- Validate Supabase JWT on every request via middleware
- Extract `user_id` and `org_id` from the authenticated session
- All queries MUST be scoped by `org_id`
- Use `permission_service.py` for role-based access checks (Owner, Admin, Estimator, Viewer)

## Patterns

- Async endpoints with `async def`
- Celery tasks in `tasks/` for heavy work (PDF processing, exports, emails)
- Log all data changes to `event_log` table via `event_service.py`
- Consistent error responses: `{"error": {"code": "...", "message": "..."}}`
- Never store raw card data -- DodoPayments handles PCI compliance
